---
import JournalEntry from '../../../layouts/JournalEntry.astro';
const base = (import.meta.env.BASE_URL || '').replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<JournalEntry
  title="Development Sprint – Quiz Fixes, Mobile Encyclopedia, ADPIE Quiz, HMAC Reveal Links & Slide Polish"
  date="2026-03-24"
  entryType="Development Log"
  course="D439 – Foundations of Nursing"
  showConceptMap={false}
>
  <p style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    Today's development sprint produced <strong>5 pull requests</strong> merged across
    quiz reliability, mobile layout, new embedded quizzes, a security-aware daily-reveal
    link system, and slide-deck polish.
  </p>

  <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem; font-weight:700; color:#1e293b; margin:1.5rem 0 0.75rem;">🐛 Bug Fixes</h2>

  <p style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
    <strong>Quiz submit/reset button fix</strong> (PR #62) — Submit and reset buttons on
    the
    <a href={`${base}/private/d439/nursing-process`} style="color:#6366f1; font-weight:600;">Nursing Process</a>
    page and all chapter quiz pages were silently doing nothing. The root cause was that
    Astro bundles inline <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> tags as ES modules with deferred
    evaluation, so <code>getElementById</code> calls at module scope ran before the DOM
    was ready. Fixed by wrapping all DOM queries in a <code>DOMContentLoaded</code>
    listener across every affected page.
  </p>

  <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem; font-weight:700; color:#1e293b; margin:1.5rem 0 0.75rem;">📱 Mobile Layout</h2>

  <p style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
    <strong>Encyclopedia mobile redesign</strong> (PR #61) — All encyclopedia article
    pages received a mobile-first layout pass (≤768px breakpoint). Both the left topic
    panel and the right TOC sidebar are now hidden on phones via
    <code>.article-grid &gt; aside &#123; display: none; &#125;</code> so the full
    viewport width is given to the article content. At the tablet breakpoint (≤1024px)
    only the right TOC sidebar collapses. CSS is applied inline in each of the 23
    article <code>.astro</code> files because Astro's scoped styles cannot be shared
    across components.
  </p>

  <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem; font-weight:700; color:#1e293b; margin:1.5rem 0 0.75rem;">📝 New Embedded Quiz</h2>

  <p style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
    <strong>ADPIE micro-quiz on the Nursing Process page</strong> (PR #60) — A
    12-question NCLEX-style micro-quiz covering the five ADPIE phases (Assessment,
    Diagnosis, Planning, Implementation, Evaluation) was embedded directly on the
    <a href={`${base}/private/d439/nursing-process`} style="color:#6366f1; font-weight:600;">Nursing Process</a>
    study page. The quiz uses the same horizontally-sliding question carousel and
    pill-shaped answer options introduced in the standalone
    <a href={`${base}/tools/quiz`} style="color:#6366f1; font-weight:600;">/tools/quiz</a>
    component.
  </p>

  <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem; font-weight:700; color:#1e293b; margin:1.5rem 0 0.75rem;">🔐 Security &amp; Access</h2>

  <p style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
    <strong>Daily-expiring per-page HMAC reveal links</strong> (PR #59) — A
    build-time HMAC token system was added to generate daily-expiring reveal links for
    individual private pages. Each link is signed with a secret key at build time and
    expires at midnight UTC, so shared links become invalid the following day. This
    gives a lightweight, no-backend way to share specific private pages with
    time-limited access without exposing the site-wide password.
  </p>

  <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem; font-weight:700; color:#1e293b; margin:1.5rem 0 0.75rem;">🖼️ Slide Polish</h2>

  <p style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    <strong>Hide legend panel on title &amp; final slides</strong> (PR #58) — The left
    legend panel that annotates slide columns was being rendered on the title slide and
    the closing summary slide, where it cluttered the layout. The panel is now hidden on
    both the first and last slides of every slide deck so those slides can use the full
    horizontal width for their content.
  </p>

  <div style="margin-top:1.5rem; background:#eef2ff; border:1px solid #c7d2fe; border-radius:0.6rem; padding:1rem 1.25rem; font-size:0.875rem; color:#3730a3; display:flex; align-items:flex-start; gap:0.65rem;">
    <span style="font-size:1.1rem; flex-shrink:0;">🔗</span>
    <span>
      <strong>Cross-references:</strong> Tools and quizzes documented above are available
      under
      <a href={`${base}/tools`} style="color:#4f46e5; font-weight:600;">WGU Nursing Tools</a>.
      The D439 private study section is accessible from the
      <a href={`${base}/private/dashboard`} style="color:#4f46e5; font-weight:600;">private dashboard</a>
      after sign-in.
    </span>
  </div>
</JournalEntry>
